HEADWORD: Mylitta
<hw>Mylitta</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <fld>(Babylonian and Assyrian
Mythology)</fld> <def>The goddess of love and fertility and war; also
called <altname>Ishtar</altname>; the counterpart of
<persfn>Ashtoreth</persfn> and <persfn>Astarte</persfn>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Ishtar.</syn>⟦br⟧
